-- Mexico Stocks: America Movil, Grupo Elektra, Homex Are Active
-- B y   P a t r i c i a   L a y a
-- 2012-07-03T15:47:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-03/mexico-stocks-america-movil-grupo-elektra-homex-are-active.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in Mexico City trading. Stock symbols are
in parentheses, and prices are as of 10:01 a.m. local time.  The  IPC index  rose 0.5 percent to 40,325.20.  America Movil SAB (AMXL)  , the wireless carrier
controlled by Mexican billionaire  Carlos Slim , fell 0.2 percent
to 17.43 pesos. The shares were cut to market perform from
outperform at Itau BBA Securities by equity analyst Gregorio Tomassi. The target price for America Movil is 18 pesos per
share.  Grupo Elektra SA (ELEKTRA*)  , the retail and banking
company controlled by billionaire Ricardo Salinas, rose 5.2
percent to 558 pesos after jumping as much as 8.4 percent in
Mexico City trading, the biggest intraday gain since June 20. On
June 19, Elektra announced it had unwound some equity
derivatives that may have been jeopardizing its position on the
benchmark index.  Desarrolladora Homex SAB (HOMEX* MM), Mexico’s largest
homebuilder, rose 3.6 percent to 35.50 pesos. This is the most
the stock has risen since June 22, when speculation rule changes
at Infonavit, the nation’s biggest mortgage provider, would
improve cash flow for builders rallied the stock 7.4 percent.  To contact the reporter on this story:
